                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">7510.92/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-07T12:00:00+07:00"
                            >September 7, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 5:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Legation’s telegram 67, September 5, 3 p.m. The Deputy Minister of Foreign
                    Affairs said his Government proposed to deal with the French authorities and not
                    with the Japanese in making its claim for the return of the territories in
                    Indo-China in the event of any change in the <hi rend="italic">status quo</hi>,
                    and further that this had been made known to the French Minister in Bangkok who
                    had been requested to transmit the Thai proposal to his Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
